<1ST_LINE>r a PM-KmartCrash     11-16 0249</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-K mart Crash,0256</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Car Crashes Into K mart, Killing One, Injuring 13</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELLEVILLE, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man whose car plowed through the aisles
of a busy department store, killing one person and injuring 13,
tried to turn around and drive out of the building after the vehicle
reached the back, a witness said.
   The motorist, 72-year-old Louis Prosperi of Bloomfield, told
police ``he had a malfunction in the car,'' Lt. Joseph Simonetti
said Tuesday. The Cadillac was impounded for mechanical tests today,
Simonetti said.
   Prosperi was questioned and released after the accident Tuesday.
No charges were filed.
   The car crashed through the plate-glass front doors of a K mart
store around 2 p.m. and traveled about 100 feet, sending glass,
concrete, employees and customers into the air, Simonetti said.
   ``I just saw everybody flying,'' said Helen Romano, who was
standing outside. Ms. Romano said that after the car came to a stop
near the back of the store, Prosperi tried to turn it around and
drive out of the building.
   Clothing, cameras and jewelry were strewn across the store after
the accident. Aisles were demolished and black skid marks left on
the floor.
   Barbara Urbanovick, 37, of Nutley was pronounced dead at the
scene. Dorothy Becker, 65, was listed in guarded condition at
University Hospital in Newark.
   Twelve others were in stable condition at Clara Maass Medical
Center, three with leg and hip fractures and the rest with cuts and
bruises, said hospital spokesman Lew Gardner.
</TEXT>
