<1ST_LINE>r a PM-SkinheadsBeating     11-16 0465</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Skinheads Beating,0479</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Federal Authorities Join Investigation Of Skinhead-Linked Fatal
Beating</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Betre is cq in 10th graf</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By CAROL ANN RIHA</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The FBI and U.S. attorney's office have
joined the investigation into an attack by suspected
white-supremacist ``skinheads'' that left a black man dead and two
others injured, a federal prosecutor says.
   Mulugeta Seraw, a 27-year-old Ethiopian immigrant, died after
being beaten with a baseball bat and kicked by three men who may be
``skinheads,'' young toughs blamed for violence against minorities
around the nation, police said.
   Two other Ethiopian men, friends who had dropped Seraw off in
front of his apartment early Sunday, were injured when they tried to
intervene.
   Police said the attackers had shaved heads and wore military
jackets. Investigators had no other leads, police spokesman Dave
Simpson said Tuesday.
   U.S. Attorney Charles Turner said investigators would try to
determine ``whether there were any ties by the assailants to
individuals or organizations outside the state and, number two,
focus on the racial aspects of the killing.''
   Elsewhere, five teen-agers who appeared to be linked to the
skinhead movement were arrested in the vandalizing of a synagogue in
San Diego. Police said swastikas and hate slogans were painted on
the outside walls of Tiffereth Israel Synagogue early Sunday, and
two cars and a home nearby were damaged.
   ``They talked a little bit (during questioning) about skinhead
activity and their knowledge of skinheads, so we think they're
affiliated,'' said San Diego police Capt. Mike Tyler. ``I certainly
see that whole skinhead ideology (in the incident).'' He added that
except for one girl, they ``were not remorseful at all.''
   The five, all 16, were booked for investigation of felony
vandalisim of a place of worship with intent to intimidate.
   In Portland, Turner said that filing of federal civil rights
charges would be considered only if state officials failed to pursue
the more serious homicide charges. ``And I don't expect that in this
case,'' he added.
   ``Mr. Turner has been very cooperative with us,'' said Betre
Melles of the Ethiopian Community Organization. ``I think that sends
a message to the community.''
   Seraw's uncle, Engedaw Berhanu of San Francisco, said the attack
on his nephew was unprovoked. ``I don't think we have any doubt that
a brutal murder has been committed by some racial hate group,'' he
said.
   ``Of course, it leaves us (blacks) in fear and uncertainty,'' he
said.
   Seraw immigrated from Ethiopia seven years ago and worked at a
car rental business.
   Skinheads have been linked to at least two other slayings: the
beating death in December of a black man in Tampa, Fla., and the
stabbing in February of a white man who took a black friend to a
party in Santa Clara County, Calif.
</TEXT>
