<2ND_LINE>PM-Elvis Abduction,0184</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Elvis Look-Alike Abducts Student</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAMPA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A teen-ager says a man bearing a striking
resemblance to Elvis Presley forced her at gunpoint to drive to
Alabama and sang along with the radio during the trip.
   ``He might have looked like Elvis, but he sure didn't sing like
him,'' University of South Florida freshman Wendy Durgan said after
returning safely to her parents' Tampa home Tuesday.
   Ms. Durgan, 18, said she was abducted Sunday in the parking lot
of the restaurant where she worked as a waitress. She said the man
kept the gun in his hand throughout the 10-hour trip but didn't
point it at her once they were on the road.
   The gunman directed the young woman to drive to the Birmingham
Municipal Airport, where he told her to go inside and wait. When she
returned with an airport officer, the car was there but the man was
gone, she said.
   FBI agents were looking for a man in his early to mid-30s.
Investigators had no motive and few leads, said agent Lou Brannon.
</TEXT>
