<HEAD>Milwaukee Man Shoots State Trooper, Security Guard, Self</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELVIDERE, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man wanted for attempted murder in
Wisconsin wounded a state trooper and a security guard early today,
then shot himself in the head as police closed in, authorities said.
   The gunman, Phuoc Tri Nguyen, 36, and Trooper Jose Rangel, 33,
were in critical condition, while the security guard was treated for
an arm wound, said Trooper Glenn Koski, a police spokesman.
   Nguyen also robbed a Belvidere service station during the crime
spree, locking an attendant in a washroom and taking $160, said Sgt.
Tami Haukedahl.
   ``They said he (Nguyen) lost his job and kind of went bananas,''
said Haukedahl. It was not immediately known how Nguyen was employed.
   Police had sought Nguyen in the shooting Sunday of his landlord,
John Pietruscka, said Milwaukee police Lt. David Brues. Pietruscka,
74, was listed in critical condition today.
   The string of shootings began early today, Haukedahl said, when
Nguyen failed to pay a toll on Interstate 90. Rangel followed the
car and was shot in the abdomen when he approached, she said.
   Rangel and his partner returned fire, but the car sped off.
Minutes later, Nguyen drove to a car dealership, where he was
confronted by Michael T. Glee, an 18-year-old security guard. Nguyen
shot Glee, Haukedahl said.
   About 2:15 a.m., Nguyen robbed a gas station, Haukedahl said.
   Shortly afternward, a Belvidere patrolman pulled over Nguyen's
car. Nguyen shot himself in the head after backup police officers
arrived, Haukedahl said.
