<HEAD>Mother Accused of Trying to Sell Baby for $550 For Dad's Bail Money</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman offered to sell her 3-month-old daughter to
two undercover officers for $550 so she could bail her husband out
of jail, police said.
   Zenobia Morales, 18, was arrested Tuesday on suspicion of selling
a child and was jailed on $3,500 bail, authorities said.
   Two police officers posing as a married couple interested in
buying an infant visited Mrs. Morales after receiving an anonymous
call Tuesday from a person who said the mother wanted to sell the
baby, police said.
   Mrs. Morales told the officers the bail bondsman would take $600
cash, but she accepted $550, wrapping the infant in a blanket and
handing the baby over, police said.
   Her daughter and her two other children _ ages 18 months and 3
years _ were taken into state custody.
   Her husband, Francisco Morales, 27, has been held since Thursday
on $4,715 bail on a charge of burglary of a motor vehicle and
several misdemeanors.
   Baby selling carries a maximum penalty of 10 years in prison and
a $5,000 fine.
