<HEAD>3-Year-Old Girl Found Beaten to Death, Tossed Over Fence</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSON, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 3-year-old girl was snatched from her
bed, apparently beaten to death and then tossed over a neighbor's
fence, and a man who had lived with the girl's mother was arrested
later Wednesday, police said.
   The girl apparently died of head injuries Tuesday night or
Wednesday morning, Sgt. Chip Pippen said.
   Authorities said Huey Harold McCraw Jr., 26, was arrested at a
motel in Flowood.
   A few minutes earlier, an unidentified young woman who had been
traveling with McCraw turned herself in at a south Jackson service
station, officers said. Police did not indicate whether charges
would be filed against the woman.
   ``The investigation is not complete,'' Hinds County Coroner
Robert Martin said, adding that an autopsy was ordered to determine
the cause of death.
   Police had issued an arrest warrant for McCraw, who had lived
with the girl's mother, said Sgt. Ray Reed.
   Officers said the body of Jessica Marie Putnam was discovered
Wednesday on property near the child's home after her mother
returned from work about 1:45 a.m. and found her daughter wasn't in
her bed.
   The mother, Belinda Putnam, checked with her 15-year-old son, who
was in bed in another room, and then double-checked the house.
   The telephone rang after Putnam had been home a few mintues, and
an unidentified female caller asked her if Jessica was OK and in her
bedroom, Pippen said. The caller hung up after telling Putnam to
``check the backyard.''
