<HEAD>Nigerian Diplomat's Husband Charged With Drug Smuggling</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The husband of a Nigerian diplomat has
been charged with smuggling marijuana into Zimbabwe and bribing a
customs official, a newspaper reported Wednesday.
   The trial of Oluromiti Joseph, 28, who is married to a Nigerian
High Commission diplomat, opened in Harare on Tuesday, The Herald
reported.
   Joseph, who pleaded innocent, faces a maximum sentence of 12
years in prison if convicted.
   The state claims Joseph and a Nigerian friend smuggled 38 pounds
of marijuana into Harare airport in suitcases with false bottoms.
Joseph allegedly offered a $300 bribe to a customs officer who found
the drugs, the newspaper said.
   Joseph's friend, Lookman Abioudun, was convicted of smuggling and
sentenced to three years in prison earlier this month.
