<HEAD>Belgium Lowers Discount, Lombard Rates</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Belgian central bank announced Wednesday it
was cutting its discount and Lombard rates, effective Thursday.
   The discount rate was being lowered by a quarter of a percentage
point to 7.25 percent from 7.5 percent and the Lombard was being cut
by the same margin to 7.5 percent from 7.75 percent.
   This is the first time the two rates have been lowered since
August.
   The discount rate is the rate of interest used by banks for
discount commercial paper at the central bank. The Lombard rate is
the amount charged on advances to banks where securities are used as
collateral.
</TEXT>
