<HEAD>London Shares Close Higher</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Updates thruout with closing figures.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
  - Share prices finished slightly higher Wednesday
after a moderately active session on the London Stock Exchange.
   London equities moved up in the early afternoon on news that
Britain's General Electric Co. and Siemens AG of West Germany
launched a takeover bid for British electronics giant Plessey Co.
PLC.
   But prices later sank in tandem with prices on Wall Street.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index rose 5 points,
or 0.3 percent, to 1,807.3. The Financial Times 30-share index rose
16.2 points to 1,477.1.
   Volume was a moderate 549 million shares, compared with the 344.7
million shares traded Tuesday.
   The Financial Times 500-share index rose 3.22 points to close at
1,029.33.
